  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).",
    "Season the lamb with salt, pepper, and ground cumin.",
    "Mix olive oil, flour, baking powder, cayenne pepper, lemon zest, thyme leaves, rosemary sprigs, and remaining spices in a small bowl.",
    "Dip your fingers into the spice mixture and rub over both sides of each piece of lamb. Place seasoned lamb on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "Roast for 1 hour or until internal temperature reaches 145°F (63°C).",
    "Rest the lamb under foil for at least 10 minutes before slicing."
